CREATED:20140501T184815Z
DESCRIPTION:Dagger\, Flow and Mortar are open source libraries that form th
 e backbone of Square's flagship Register app. Use them to spend less time f
 ighting the life cycle and more time coding (and unit testing).\n\nRay Ryan
  is a senior software citizen at Square\, where he focuses on making Androi
 d development tolerable. He has been goading people into writing software t
 he way he thinks they should since the 1980s.\n\nThanks to:\n\n- Ray & Amer
 ican Express for booking the lovely auditorium!\n\n- Michael at American Ex
 press for inviting and flying Ray out\n\n- Ray Ryan for flying out for our 
 meetup!\n\nRay's talk will begin promptly at 7:15pm.\n\nAuditorium doesn't 
 allow food/beverages\, so grab a quick bite after work!\n\nAfter party venu
 e to be determined.\n\nDetails: http://www.meetup.com/android-developers-ny
 c/events/179011832/
LAST-MODIFIED:20140501T184815Z
LOCATION:200 Vesey Street\, New York\, NY
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Ray Ryan talks Square APIs
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
